{{wikipedia|dab=apex|lang=en}}

===Etymology===
From {{etyl|la|en}} {{term|lang=la|apex||point, tip, summit}}.

===Pronunciation===
* {{a|UK|US}} {{IPA|/ˈeɪ.pɛks/|lang=en}}

===Noun===
{{en-noun|apices|apexes}}

# The highest point of something.
#: ''the '''apex''' of the building''
# {{context|figuratively|lang=en}} The moment of greatest [[success]], [[expansion]], etc.
#: ''the '''apex''' of civilization''
#* '''2002''', [[w:Jeffrey Rowland|Jeffrey Rowland]], [http://jjrowland.com/wigu/20020327.html WIGU adventures]
#*: It would be an intense disgust.  The absolute '''apex''' of teen angst.
# {{context|geometry|lang=en}} The topmost [[vertex]] of a [[cone]] or [[pyramid]] (in their conventional orientation).
# {{context|chiefly|anatomy|lang=en}} The [[pointed]] end of something.
## The [[low]]est part of the human [[heart]].
## The [[deep]]est part of a [[tooth]]'s [[root]].
# {{context|botany|lang=en}} The end of a [[leaf]], [[petal]] or similar organ opposed to the end where it is attached to its support; the [[tip]].
# {{context|astronomy|lang=en}} The point on the celestial sphere toward which the sun appears to move relative to nearby stars.
# {{context|physics|lang=en}} The lowest point on a pendant drop of a liquid.
# {{context|mining|US|lang=en}} The end or edge of a [[vein]] nearest the [[surface]].<!--Webster 1913-->

